						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the temple of Gangamma.</p>						

						<p>Dated <hi rend="italic">Nala, Nija Āśvīja,</hi> śu. 15 (Written in late characters).</p>						

						<p>States that Pōtaya, son of Veṅgaḷa, the priest performed the jaṁḍalu services (?) in the temple. (See <hi rend="italic">N.D.I.</hi> Part I, Darśi 17, p. 308).</p>						

